.TH GEOM_BLANKET 1 2026-Jan "" "Create monochromatic overlay for MS imaging"
.SH NAME
geom_blanket \- geom_blanket(mz,
    <i>tolerance</i> = 'getOption'('mzdiff', 'default' = 'da:0.3'))
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fIgeom_blanket(mz,
    <i>tolerance</i> = 'getOption'('mzdiff', 'default' = 'da:0.3'))\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Generates a grayscale ggplot2 layer for mass spectrometry imaging (MSI) data,
typically used as a background layer or for intensity normalization.
.PP
.SH OPTIONS
.PP
\fBmz\fB \fR\- . numeric. The target mass-to-charge ratio (m/z) value for ion detection.
.PP
.PP
\fBtolerance\fB \fR\- 'getOption'('mzdiff', 'default' = 'da:0.3'). character or numeric. Mass accuracy tolerance. See geom_red() for format details.
.PP
.SH VALUE
.PP
A ggplot2 layer object using "Greys" color palette with alpha channel (c8 = 200/255 transparency)
suitable for creating intensity-normalized backgrounds or composite overlays.
.PP
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
#\dontrun{

plot_base() + geom_blanket(1200.834)

#}
.PP
